■ Acetic Acid
■ Definition:
A simple carboxylic acid with the formula CH■COOH. Commonly found in vinegar.
■ Key Concepts:
- Weak acid with pKa ~ 4.76
- Found in vinegar
- Used in food preservation and chemical synthesis
■ Memory Aid:
Think of vinegar! Acetic = acidic!
